Collection classes for this library

          Description

Interface Summary
ContainerFactory Allows for mocking of Class.newInstance() for containers.
SequentialAccess Opposite of RandomAccess.
Tuple<TValue> N-element tuple, which may be empty.
 

Class Summary
AbstractTuple<TValue> Abstract super class for tuples.
ArrayAsFixedSizeList<TValue> This class combines features of FixedSizeForwardingList with Arrays.asList(Object[]).
ArrayAsImmutableList<TValue> This class has the same effect as: Collections.unmodifiableList(Arrays.asList(arr.clone())).
ArrayAsUnmodifiableList<TValue> This class has the same effect as: Collections.unmodifiableList(Arrays.asList(arr)).
BaseFixedSizeForwardingList<TValue> This is a base class used by FixedSizeForwardingList and UnmodifiableForwardingList.
ByteArraySimpleBuilder Very simple class to build a byte array: byte[].
ContainerFactoryImpl Stateless factory for any Java container.
FixedSizeForwardingList<TValue> This is a specialized form of ForwardingList that does not allow the underlying list size to change.
FixedSizeListIterator<TValue> This class is a simple extension of ForwardingListIterator, where methods FixedSizeListIterator.add(Object) and FixedSizeListIterator.remove() are disabled -- always throw UnsupportedOperationException.
Lists2 More static utility methods for List.
UnmodifiableForwardingIterator<TValue> This class is a simple extension of ForwardingIterator, where method UnmodifiableForwardingIterator.remove() is disabled -- always throws UnsupportedOperationException.
UnmodifiableForwardingList<TValue> This is a specialized form of ForwardingList that does not allow the underlying list to change.
UnmodifiableForwardingListIterator<TValue> This class is a simple extension of ForwardingListIterator, where methods UnmodifiableForwardingListIterator.add(Object), UnmodifiableForwardingListIterator.remove(), and UnmodifiableForwardingListIterator.set(Object) are disabled -- always throw UnsupportedOperationException.
